content:
One is what one thinks;
Thinking is what one's thoughts are;
One is what one's thoughts are.

..Seldom,
In admiration of them..;
What thou hast in thy mind,
I see not in thine eyes;
What thou sayest,
I see not in thy mind..

The most idyllic eternity is with love;
the most antagonistic hell is with hate;
So be loving and guard against hate.

The tale of love is settled in the moon;
Beauty is mythologized with the moon;
Every phase has its zestful sway,
To make us fond of the moon...

Sometimes having no reason for reasoning is
better than having some reasons;
such an unconditional state.
